steps.instruction:
For a more step by step guide go [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2009/01/08/white-bread-pure-and-simple)

### Mixing and Kneading
1. Combine all of the ingredients, mix and knead using your hands or a stand mixer till a smooth soft dough forms
2. Transfer the dough to a lightly greased bowl and cover. Allow to rise till very puffy (about 1.5 hours)

### Shaping
1. Lightly grease a 13" pain de mie pan
2. Gently deflate the dough and transfer it to a lightly greased work surface
3. Shape it into a 13" log and fit it into the pan
4. Cover the pan with lightly greased plastic wrap
5. Allow to rise till its just below the lip of the pan (about 45 minutes to an hour)
    - Near the end of the rise, preheat your oven to 350F

### Baking
6. Remove the plastic wrap and place the cover on the pan
7. Bake the bread for 25 minutes
8. Remove from the oven and carefully remove the lid
9. Put the loaf back into the oven for another 20 minutes, or until the center registers 190F
10. Remove the bread and allow it to cool completely on a wire rack
